Sentencas: GdBaCo2O5+delta (GBCO) powders were synthesized by the glycine-nitrate process (GNP) with different glycine/metal ratios (G/M) and characterized as cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell(IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Synthesis and Characterization of GdBaCo2O5+δ Cathode Material by Glycine-nitrate Process

Sentencas: The effects of G/M ratios on the performance and properties of GBCO electrodes including the morphology, crystal structure, electrical conductivity and electrochemical properties were evaluated.
Titulo: Synthesis and Characterization of GdBaCo2O5+δ Cathode Material by Glycine-nitrate Process

Sentencas: The GBCO powder synthesized at G/M ratio of 3.0 (GBCO-3.0) showed the highest specific surface area.
Titulo: Synthesis and Characterization of GdBaCo2O5+δ Cathode Material by Glycine-nitrate Process

Sentencas: XRD results proved that the precursor powders calcined at 1000 degrees C for 5 h formed GBCO single-phase when the ratio of glycine to metal was in the range of 2.5-3.5.
Titulo: Synthesis and Characterization of GdBaCo2O5+δ Cathode Material by Glycine-nitrate Process

Sentencas: There were no chemical reaction occurred between the GBCO cathode and the Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) electrolyte after calcination at 1100 degrees C.
Titulo: Synthesis and Characterization of GdBaCo2O5+δ Cathode Material by Glycine-nitrate Process

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities of all GBCO cathodes were over 100 S/cm at intermediate temperature (500-800 degrees C).
Titulo: Synthesis and Characterization of GdBaCo2O5+δ Cathode Material by Glycine-nitrate Process

Sentencas: The GBCO-3.0 cathode calcined at 1050 degrees C exhibited the lowest polarization resistance (R-P) of 0.125 Omega.cm(2) at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Synthesis and Characterization of GdBaCo2O5+δ Cathode Material by Glycine-nitrate Process
